(number unknown), of both sexes, up to 16-mm long; held in the Museo civico di Storia naturale, Genova, without catalogue number.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0B5736F35B53FF94FF62FD83FF3F2276" blockId="20.[144,759,626,1046]" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis id="399CEAE15B53FF94FF62FD83FEC824E8" box="[144,262,627,648]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
<collectionCode id="6DF9AE365B53FF94FEE1FD82FEEB24E7" box="[275,293,626,647]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15406" name="Harvard University - Arnold Arboretum" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" type="Herbarium">A</collectionCode>
<taxonomicName id="CCE84D705B53FF94FEDDFD83FDDC24E8" box="[303,530,626,648]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Stenotaenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="399CEAE15B53FF94FEDDFD83FE7B24E8" box="[303,437,627,648]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">Stenotaenia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
of small body size (total length not reaching 
<quantity id="CC109B165B53FF94FE30FD61FE3524C6" box="[450,507,657,678]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" unit="cm" value="2.0">2 cm</quantity>
); 
<emphasis id="399CEAE15B53FF94FDE2FD62FDD524C7" box="[528,539,658,679]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">c</emphasis>
. 43–49 leg-bearing segments; labrum with about one or two tubercles; first maxillae without distinct lappets on both the coxosternum and the telopodites; chitin lines of the forcipular coxosternum not reaching the anterior condyles; anterior margin of the forcipular coxosternum angulated; forcipular intermediate articles distinct; sternal pore areas in the anterior part of the trunk oval, longer than wide, and placed on the posterior half of each sternum; each coxopleuron with one anterior pouch with pores and one posterior single pore or a pouch with very few pores (see also 
<tableCitation id="466A03485B53FF94FF62FBF0FF2A2276" box="[144,228,1024,1046]" captionStart="Table 3" captionStartId="8.[144,208,438,459]" captionText="Table 3. Characters of possible diagnostic value for the species referred here to Stenotaenia" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">Table 3</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0B5736F35B53FF94FF62FBCEFE702349" blockId="20.[144,759,1085,1321]" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis id="399CEAE15B53FF94FF62FBCEFEA42232" box="[144,362,1085,1107]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">Taxonomic history:</emphasis>
After the original description by 
<bibRefCitation id="6F794B025B53FF94FF62FBACFE842212" author="Silvestri F" box="[144,330,1116,1138]" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" pagination="191 - 201" refId="ref25282" refString="Silvestri F. 1895. Contribuzione alla conoscenza dei Chilopodi, Symphyli, Pauropodi e Diplopodi dell'Umbria e del Lazio. Bollettino della Societa Romana per gli Studi Zoologici 3: 191 - 201." type="journal article" year="1895">Silvestri (1895)</bibRefCitation>
the true identity of this species remained uncertain until 
<bibRefCitation id="6F794B025B53FF94FE3AFB8AFD4522F1" author="Minelli A" box="[456,651,1146,1169]" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref24473" refString="Minelli A. 1983 a. On Sardinian centipedes (Chilopoda). Bollettino di Zoologia 49 (1982): 1 - 16." type="journal article" year="1983">Minelli’s (1983a)</bibRefCitation>
account, based upon the examination of the 
<typeStatus id="D45388515B53FF94FDBCFB69FDB122CE" box="[590,639,1177,1198]" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">type</typeStatus>
material. 
<taxonomicName id="CCE84D705B53FF94FF62FB48FEBF22AD" authorityName="Silvestri" authorityYear="1895" box="[144,369,1208,1229]" class="Chilopoda" family="Geophilidae" genus="Geophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Geophilomorpha" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="romanus">
<emphasis id="399CEAE15B53FF94FF62FB48FEBF22AD" box="[144,369,1208,1229]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">Geophilus romanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recorded from other Italian localities (
<bibRefCitation id="6F794B025B53FF94FEF5FB26FE7F228B" author="Minelli A" box="[263,433,1238,1260]" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref24473" refString="Minelli A. 1983 a. On Sardinian centipedes (Chilopoda). Bollettino di Zoologia 49 (1982): 1 - 16." type="journal article" year="1983">Minelli, 1983a</bibRefCitation>
, 1992; 
<bibRefCitation id="6F794B025B53FF94FDFAFB26FF07236B" author="Minelli A &amp; Zapparoli M" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" pagination="373 - 411" refId="ref24695" refString="Minelli A, Zapparoli M. 1985. I Chilopodi della regione ligure con particolare riguardo al popolamento delle Alpi Liguri. Lavori della Societa Italiana di Biogeografia N. S. 9 (1982): 373 - 411." type="journal article" year="1985">Minelli &amp; Zapparoli, 1985</bibRefCitation>
, 1992), but its assignment to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="CCE84D705B53FF94FD6CFB05FF7C2348" baseAuthorityName="Verhoeff" baseAuthorityYear="1924" class="Chilopoda" family="Geophilidae" genus="Geophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Geophilomorpha" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="399CEAE15B53FF94FD6CFB05FF7C2348" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">Geophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was never questioned.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0B5736F35B53FF94FF62FAA1FB792757" blockId="20.[144,759,1361,1903]" lastBlockId="20.[806,1421,198,312]" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis id="399CEAE15B53FF94FF62FAA1FEFC2306" box="[144,306,1361,1382]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">Assignment to</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="CCE84D705B53FF94FECEFAA1FE292306" authority=": It" authorityName="It" box="[316,487,1361,1382]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Stenotaenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="399CEAE15B53FF94FECEFAA1FE072306" box="[316,457,1361,1382]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">Stenotaenia:</emphasis>
It
</taxonomicName>
is assigned confidently to 
<taxonomicName id="CCE84D705B53FF94FF41FA80FEF723E5" box="[179,313,1392,1413]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Stenotaenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="399CEAE15B53FF94FF41FA80FEF723E5" box="[179,313,1392,1413]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">Stenotaenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="399CEAE15B53FF94FEBCFA9FFE1723E4" bold="true" box="[334,473,1391,1412]" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">comb. nov.</emphasis>
), based on the original description, as emendated by 
<bibRefCitation id="6F794B025B53FF94FDC6FA7EFD3823C4" author="Minelli A" box="[564,758,1422,1444]" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref24473" refString="Minelli A. 1983 a. On Sardinian centipedes (Chilopoda). Bollettino di Zoologia 49 (1982): 1 - 16." type="journal article" year="1983">Minelli (1983a)</bibRefCitation>
(Table 2), as well as on the examination of representative specimens from throughout the known range (
<figureCitation id="93D32A765B53FF94FF65FA1AFF10239F" box="[151,222,1514,1536]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="12.[144,223,1853,1872]" captionTargetBox="[144,1424,1186,1823]" captionTargetId="figure-424@12.[144,1424,1186,1823]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 3. Geographical distribution of Stenotaenia frenum, Stenotaenia romana, and Stenotaenia sturanyi. Both previously published and new records have been plotted upon a grid of 30′ latitude ¥ 30′ longitude." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5446078" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5446078/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">Figs 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="93D32A765B53FF94FF02FA19FF31239F" box="[240,255,1513,1535]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="17.[164,243,1105,1124]" captionTargetBox="[387,1220,195,1076]" captionTargetId="figure-329@17.[387,1220,195,1076]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 5. Microscopic images of a female specimen of Stenotaenia romana (Silvestri, 1895) from Isola del Cantone near Genova (Italy: Liguria) (12-mm long, with 47 leg-bearing segments; 5-XI-1978 Gardini lg, collection A. Minelli): (a) head, ventral; (b) clypeus and maxillary complex, ventral; (c) sternum of leg-bearing segment X; (d) forcipular segment, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5446082" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5446082/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">5</figureCitation>
). This species shares all major diagnostic characters of the genus, including the shape of the labrum, the features of the maxillary complex and the mandibles, the general shape of the forcipular segment, the pattern of sternal pore areas and of the coxal pores, and the features of the legs of the last pair. It is worth noting that 
<bibRefCitation id="6F794B025B53FF94FE24F951FD5820D7" author="Silvestri F" box="[470,662,1697,1719]" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" pagination="191 - 201" refId="ref25282" refString="Silvestri F. 1895. Contribuzione alla conoscenza dei Chilopodi, Symphyli, Pauropodi e Diplopodi dell'Umbria e del Lazio. Bollettino della Societa Romana per gli Studi Zoologici 3: 191 - 201." type="journal article" year="1895">Silvestri’s (1895)</bibRefCitation>
original description was inaccurate in recognizing only a single pore on the internal ventral side of each coxopleuron, whereas an anterior pouch is also invariantly present, as demonstrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="6F794B025B53FF94FDB3F8ECFD382152" author="Minelli A" box="[577,758,1820,1842]" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref24473" refString="Minelli A. 1983 a. On Sardinian centipedes (Chilopoda). Bollettino di Zoologia 49 (1982): 1 - 16." type="journal article" year="1983">Minelli (1983a)</bibRefCitation>
in the 
<typeStatus id="D45388515B53FF94FF10F8CBFEDD2130" box="[226,275,1851,1872]" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">type</typeStatus>
material, and confirmed by our original observations in other specimens. The affinity between 
<taxonomicName id="CCE84D705B53FF94FCD4FF36FC5226BB" baseAuthorityName="Silvestri" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[806,924,198,219]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Stenotaenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="romana">
<emphasis id="399CEAE15B53FF94FCD4FF36FC5226BB" box="[806,924,198,219]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">S. romana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="CCE84D705B53FF94FC29FF36FB9E26BB" authorityName=": Attems" authorityYear="1929" box="[987,1104,198,219]" class="Chilopoda" family="Geophilidae" genus="Clinopodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Geophilomorpha" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="linearis">
<emphasis id="399CEAE15B53FF94FC29FF36FB9E26BB" box="[987,1104,198,219]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">S. linearis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was already acknowledged (
<bibRefCitation id="6F794B025B53FF94FCDCFF14FC18269A" author="Silvestri F" box="[814,982,228,250]" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" pagination="191 - 201" refId="ref25282" refString="Silvestri F. 1895. Contribuzione alla conoscenza dei Chilopodi, Symphyli, Pauropodi e Diplopodi dell'Umbria e del Lazio. Bollettino della Societa Romana per gli Studi Zoologici 3: 191 - 201." type="journal article" year="1895">Silvestri, 1895</bibRefCitation>
; Minelli, 1992), and indeed 
<taxonomicName id="CCE84D705B53FF94FAE5FF15FA43269A" baseAuthorityName="Silvestri" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[1303,1421,229,250]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Stenotaenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="romana">
<emphasis id="399CEAE15B53FF94FAE5FF15FA43269A" box="[1303,1421,229,250]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">S. romana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was even suspected by 
<bibRefCitation id="6F794B025B53FF94FBB3FEF3FB3C2779" author="Verhoeff KW" box="[1089,1266,259,281]" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" pagination="228 - 286" refId="ref25798" refString="Verhoeff KW. 1928. Geophilomorphen-Beitrage und eine Lithobius - Form. Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin 14: 228 - 286." type="journal article" year="1928">Verhoeff (1928)</bibRefCitation>
to represent just a juvenile stage of 
<taxonomicName id="CCE84D705B53FF94FBCEFED2FB7F2757" authorityName=": Attems" authorityYear="1929" box="[1084,1201,290,311]" class="Chilopoda" family="Geophilidae" genus="Clinopodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Geophilomorpha" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="linearis">
<emphasis id="399CEAE15B53FF94FBCEFED2FB7F2757" box="[1084,1201,290,311]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">S. linearis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0B5736F35B53FF94FCD4FE99FC5E2414" blockId="20.[806,1421,361,628]" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis id="399CEAE15B53FF94FCD4FE99FC48271E" box="[806,902,361,382]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">Validity:</emphasis>
It is recognized here as a very distinct species: distinguished from all other known species of 
<taxonomicName id="CCE84D705B53FF94FCBAFE56FC0027DB" box="[840,974,422,443]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Stenotaenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="399CEAE15B53FF94FCBAFE56FC0027DB" box="[840,974,422,443]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">Stenotaenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the smaller body size, the lower number of trunk segments, the apparent incompleteness of the chitin lines, and the presence of an anterior pouch of coxal glands and a posterior single large pore on each coxopleuron, even in full grown specimens, which is possibly a paedomorphic trait (
<tableCitation id="466A03485B53FF94FCDCFDAEFC4D2414" box="[814,899,606,628]" captionStart="Table 3" captionStartId="8.[144,208,438,459]" captionText="Table 3. Characters of possible diagnostic value for the species referred here to Stenotaenia" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">Table 3</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0B5736F35B53FF94FCD4FD55FBE724DA" blockId="20.[806,1422,677,1341]" box="[806,1065,677,698]" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis id="399CEAE15B53FF94FCD4FD55FBE724DA" box="[806,1065,677,698]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">Remarks on synonyms</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="43F265785B53FF94FCD4FD33FC6A235D" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="0B5736F35B53FF94FCD4FD33FC6A235D" blockId="20.[806,1422,677,1341]" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">
<taxonomicName id="CCE84D705B53FF94FCD4FD33FA4724B8" authority="Verhoeff, 1928" authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1928" box="[806,1417,707,729]" class="Chilopoda" family="Geophilidae" genus="Geophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Geophilomorpha" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvestrii" subGenus="Notadenophilus">
<emphasis id="399CEAE15B53FF94FCD4FD33FC5624B8" box="[806,920,707,728]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">Geophilus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="399CEAE15B53FF94FC59FD33FB9124B8" box="[939,1119,707,728]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">Notadenophilus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="399CEAE15B53FF94FB81FD33FB1B24B8" box="[1139,1237,707,728]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">silvestrii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="6F794B025B53FF94FB12FD33FA4724B8" author="Verhoeff KW" box="[1248,1417,707,729]" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" pagination="228 - 286" refId="ref25798" refString="Verhoeff KW. 1928. Geophilomorphen-Beitrage und eine Lithobius - Form. Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin 14: 228 - 286." type="journal article" year="1928">Verhoeff, 1928</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="CCE84D705B53FF94FCD4FD12FBCA2497" authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1928" box="[806,1028,738,759]" class="Chilopoda" family="Geophilidae" genus="Geophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Geophilomorpha" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvestrii">
<emphasis id="399CEAE15B53FF94FCD4FD12FBCA2497" box="[806,1028,738,759]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">Geophilus silvestrii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation id="6F794B025B53FF94FB2CFD12FA432498" author="Verhoeff KW" box="[1246,1421,738,760]" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" pagination="228 - 286" refId="ref25798" refString="Verhoeff KW. 1928. Geophilomorphen-Beitrage und eine Lithobius - Form. Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin 14: 228 - 286." type="journal article" year="1928">Verhoeff (1928)</bibRefCitation>
from a single male from near Rome, and another specimen was later identified by the same author from Mt Argentario, along the Tyrrhenian coast (
<bibRefCitation id="6F794B025B53FF94FAAFFCCEFC7A2512" author="Verhoeff KW" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" pagination="1 - 112" refId="ref25844" refString="Verhoeff KW. 1934 a. Beitrage zur Systematik und Geographie der Chilopoden. Zoologische Jahrbucher. Abteilung fur Systematik, Okologie und Geographie der Tiere 66: 1 - 112." type="journal article" year="1934">Verhoeff, 1934a</bibRefCitation>
). Its possible synonymy under 
<taxonomicName id="CCE84D705B53FF94FAE5FCADFA432512" baseAuthorityName="Silvestri" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[1303,1421,861,882]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Stenotaenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="romana">
<emphasis id="399CEAE15B53FF94FAE5FCADFA432512" box="[1303,1421,861,882]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">S. romana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has already been claimed (
<bibRefCitation id="6F794B025B53FF94FB88FC8BFAE425F0" author="Minelli A" box="[1146,1322,891,913]" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref24473" refString="Minelli A. 1983 a. On Sardinian centipedes (Chilopoda). Bollettino di Zoologia 49 (1982): 1 - 16." type="journal article" year="1983">Minelli, 1983a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="6F794B025B53FF94FACDFC8BFC7B25CF" author="Foddai D &amp; Minelli A &amp; Scheller U &amp; Zapparoli M" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" pagination="1 - 35" refId="ref23153" refString="Foddai D, Minelli A, Scheller U, Zapparoli M. 1995. Chilopoda, Diplopoda, Pauropoda, Symphyla. In: Minelli A, Ruffo S, La Posta S, eds. Checklist delle specie della fauna italiana. Bologna: Calderini, 32: 1 - 35." type="journal article" year="1995">
Foddai 
<emphasis id="399CEAE15B53FF94FCD4FC6AFC9925CE" box="[806,855,921,943]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">et al</emphasis>
., 1995
</bibRefCitation>
). According to the detailed original description, 
<taxonomicName id="CCE84D705B53FF94FC47FC48FBF625AD" authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1928" box="[949,1080,952,973]" class="Chilopoda" family="Geophilidae" genus="Geophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Geophilomorpha" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvestrii">
<emphasis id="399CEAE15B53FF94FC47FC48FBF625AD" box="[949,1080,952,973]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">G. silvestrii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
agrees fully with 
<taxonomicName id="CCE84D705B53FF94FAE2FC48FA4825AE" baseAuthorityName="Silvestri" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[1296,1414,952,974]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Stenotaenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="romana">
<emphasis id="399CEAE15B53FF94FAE2FC48FA4825AE" box="[1296,1414,952,974]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">S. romana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, especially in body size, the number of trunk segments, and other major traits in the forcipular segment, the sternal pore areas, the coxal pores, and the last pair of legs. Furthermore, the 
<typeStatus id="D45388515B53FF94FB1FFBC3FAD02228" box="[1261,1310,1075,1096]" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">type</typeStatus>
localities of the two nominal species are only a few kilometres apart. The only putative diagnostic difference is in the elongation of the head, but the length-to-width ratio given by Verhoeff for 
<taxonomicName id="CCE84D705B53FF94FBEFFB5DFB6E22A2" authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1928" box="[1053,1184,1197,1218]" class="Chilopoda" family="Geophilidae" genus="Geophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Geophilomorpha" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvestrii">
<emphasis id="399CEAE15B53FF94FBEFFB5DFB6E22A2" box="[1053,1184,1197,1218]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">G. silvestrii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is hardly correct, as it is outside the known range of all 
<taxonomicName id="CCE84D705B53FF94FB07FB3BFAA92280" baseAuthorityName="Verhoeff" baseAuthorityYear="1924" box="[1269,1383,1227,1248]" class="Chilopoda" family="Geophilidae" genus="Geophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Geophilomorpha" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="399CEAE15B53FF94FB07FB3BFAA92280" box="[1269,1383,1227,1248]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">Geophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="CCE84D705B53FF94FCD4FB1AFBDC2360" box="[806,1042,1258,1280]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Stenotaenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="399CEAE15B53FF94FCD4FB1AFC62229F" box="[806,940,1258,1279]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">Stenotaenia</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
Therefore, we are confident in recognizing 
<taxonomicName id="CCE84D705B53FF94FC4FFAF9FB8E237E" authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1928" box="[957,1088,1289,1310]" class="Chilopoda" family="Geophilidae" genus="Geophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Geophilomorpha" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvestrii">
<emphasis id="399CEAE15B53FF94FC4FFAF9FB8E237E" box="[957,1088,1289,1310]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">G. silvestrii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="CCE84D705B53FF94FCD4FAD8FC52235D" baseAuthorityName="Silvestri" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[806,924,1320,1341]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Stenotaenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="romana">
<emphasis id="399CEAE15B53FF94FCD4FAD8FC52235D" box="[806,924,1320,1341]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">S. romana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="43F265785B53FF94FCD4FA9EFAEA2019" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="0B5736F35B53FF94FCD4FA9EFAEA2019" blockId="20.[806,1421,1390,1657]" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis id="399CEAE15B53FF94FCD4FA9EFC7623E3" box="[806,952,1390,1411]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">Distribution:</emphasis>
It occurs mainly along the Italian Peninsula, most frequently on the Tyrrhenian side from 
<collectingRegion id="C92CF8115B53FF94FCD4FA5CFCB523A2" box="[806,891,1452,1474]" country="Italy" name="Liguria" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">Liguria</collectingRegion>
to 
<collectingRegion id="C92CF8115B53FF94FC54FA5CFBD023A2" box="[934,1054,1452,1474]" country="Italy" name="Campania" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">Campania</collectingRegion>
, including some minor islands, namely Elba, Giglio, and Ischia (new localities, see Appendix; M. Zapparoli, pers. comm.). It also occurs in 
<collectingRegion id="C92CF8115B53FF94FCBFF9F7FC61207D" box="[845,943,1543,1565]" country="Italy" name="Sardegna" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">Sardinia</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="6F794B025B53FF94FC35F9F7FBB6207E" author="Minelli A" box="[967,1144,1543,1566]" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref24473" refString="Minelli A. 1983 a. On Sardinian centipedes (Chilopoda). Bollettino di Zoologia 49 (1982): 1 - 16." type="journal article" year="1983">Minelli, 1983a</bibRefCitation>
), in the western Alps (
<bibRefCitation id="6F794B025B53FF94FCDCF9D6FBA8205C" author="Minelli A &amp; Zapparoli M" box="[814,1126,1574,1596]" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" pagination="211 - 243" refId="ref24736" refString="Minelli A, Zapparoli M. 1992. Considerazioni faunistiche e zoogeografiche sui Chilopodi delle Alpi Occidentali. Biogeographia 16: 211 - 243." type="journal article" year="1992">Minelli &amp; Zapparoli, 1992</bibRefCitation>
), on the Euganean Hills (Minelli, 1992), and on Mt Conero along the Adriatic coast (new localities, see Appendix) (
<figureCitation id="93D32A765B53FF94FB27F993FAD92019" box="[1237,1303,1635,1657]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="12.[144,223,1853,1872]" captionTargetBox="[144,1424,1186,1823]" captionTargetId="figure-424@12.[144,1424,1186,1823]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 3. Geographical distribution of Stenotaenia frenum, Stenotaenia romana, and Stenotaenia sturanyi. Both previously published and new records have been plotted upon a grid of 30′ latitude ¥ 30′ longitude." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5446078" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5446078/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="273">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
